moves.1. e4:
In this game i was playing someone rated a lot higher than me in a club match.
I like to try out this opening occasionally as it's surprising how many people actually take before they look.
I win around 50% of games when I play this one.
This is one of my all time favourites
(it's also my first time annotating!)
moves.1... e5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. f4: I Like doing this, for some reason it confuses people....
moves.4. e5:
Didn't see that coming did they?
The knight now has nowhere to go....
moves.5. Nf3: Move five and Blacks only appear to have moved one piece
moves.5... Be7: Hoping to recover with a nasty looking check
moves.6. Bc4: Setting up a square to run, i mean strategically move to.
moves.7. Kf1 Nc6 8. d4: I like that pawn where it is, thank you
moves.8... Qe7 9. Bxf4 b6 10. Nd5: And this is where it really starts falling apart!
moves.10... Qd8 11. Nxh4 Qxh4 12. c3 Qd8 13. Q:
My opponent looked so happy when he made this move.
Mate in three though
moves.17. Nxc7+ Qxc7 18. Qxf7+ Kd8 19. Qf8#: The moral of this game?  Don't be greedy!!
